.TH "__devm_pci_epc_create" 9 "__devm_pci_epc_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__devm_pci_epc_create \- create a new endpoint controller (EPC) device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct pci_epc *" __devm_pci_epc_create
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct pci_epc_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "struct module *owner "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device that is creating the new EPC
.IP "ops" 12
function pointers for performing EPC operations
.IP "owner" 12
the owner of the module that creates the EPC device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Invoke to create a new EPC device and add it to pci_epc class.
While at that, it also associates the device with the pci_epc using devres.
On driver detach, release function is invoked on the devres data,
then, devres data is freed.
